<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,908,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1160,1187]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Description.</emphasis>
Male greyish yellow with dark pattern (
<figureCitation box="[794,932,1161,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,427,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,409,1871]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–40. 23–33—Macropsis nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n. (23–24—dorsolateral view; 25, 31—lateral view; 26–27, 32— dorsal view; 28–30, 33—face; 23–30—male; 31–33—female); 34–40—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. (34, 36, 39–40—lateral view; 35—dorsal view; 37—dorsolateral view; 38—face; 34–38—male; 39–40—female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772391/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 23–30</figureCitation>
). Face yellow, in upper part with black transverse stripe interrupted in middle (
<figureCitation box="[533,616,1197,1223]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,427,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,409,1871]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–40. 23–33—Macropsis nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n. (23–24—dorsolateral view; 25, 31—lateral view; 26–27, 32— dorsal view; 28–30, 33—face; 23–30—male; 31–33—female); 34–40—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. (34, 36, 39–40—lateral view; 35—dorsal view; 37—dorsolateral view; 38—face; 34–38—male; 39–40—female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772391/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). In dark coloured specimens there are also two small black dots on crown and/or two black spots under transverse stripe (
<figureCitation box="[692,832,1233,1259]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,427,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,409,1871]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–40. 23–33—Macropsis nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n. (23–24—dorsolateral view; 25, 31—lateral view; 26–27, 32— dorsal view; 28–30, 33—face; 23–30—male; 31–33—female); 34–40—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. (34, 36, 39–40—lateral view; 35—dorsal view; 37—dorsolateral view; 38—face; 34–38—male; 39–40—female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772391/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 28–29</figureCitation>
). Pronotum greyish with yellow lateral margins. Mesonotum usually with more or less developed triangular dark spots in lateral angles and light yellow middle stripe (
<figureCitation box="[160,246,1305,1331]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,427,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,409,1871]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–40. 23–33—Macropsis nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n. (23–24—dorsolateral view; 25, 31—lateral view; 26–27, 32— dorsal view; 28–30, 33—face; 23–30—male; 31–33—female); 34–40—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. (34, 36, 39–40—lateral view; 35—dorsal view; 37—dorsolateral view; 38—face; 34–38—male; 39–40—female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772391/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). In light coloured males these spots indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[796,936,1304,1331]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,427,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,409,1871]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–40. 23–33—Macropsis nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n. (23–24—dorsolateral view; 25, 31—lateral view; 26–27, 32— dorsal view; 28–30, 33—face; 23–30—male; 31–33—female); 34–40—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. (34, 36, 39–40—lateral view; 35—dorsal view; 37—dorsolateral view; 38—face; 34–38—male; 39–40—female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772391/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 25, 27</figureCitation>
), in darker males they brown or even black (
<figureCitation box="[159,295,1341,1368]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,427,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,409,1871]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–40. 23–33—Macropsis nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n. (23–24—dorsolateral view; 25, 31—lateral view; 26–27, 32— dorsal view; 28–30, 33—face; 23–30—male; 31–33—female); 34–40—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. (34, 36, 39–40—lateral view; 35—dorsal view; 37—dorsolateral view; 38—face; 34–38—male; 39–40—female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772391/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 24, 26</figureCitation>
). Occasionally, these spots merge with each other, so that mesonotum becomes entirely brown or black with yellow lateral margins. Proepimeron always with black spot. Forewing semi-transparent, slightly smoky, with partially darkened veins, especially, in apical parts.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,908,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
Female entirely yellowish green, usually with whitish median stripe on mesonotum; very rarely with black spot on proepimeron (
<figureCitation box="[345,482,1485,1511]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,427,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,409,1871]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–40. 23–33—Macropsis nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n. (23–24—dorsolateral view; 25, 31—lateral view; 26–27, 32— dorsal view; 28–30, 33—face; 23–30—male; 31–33—female); 34–40—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. (34, 36, 39–40—lateral view; 35—dorsal view; 37—dorsolateral view; 38—face; 34–38—male; 39–40—female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772391/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 31–33</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,908,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
Apex of crown and anterior margin of pronotum rounded (
<figureCitation box="[878,1062,1521,1547]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,427,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,409,1871]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–40. 23–33—Macropsis nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n. (23–24—dorsolateral view; 25, 31—lateral view; 26–27, 32— dorsal view; 28–30, 33—face; 23–30—male; 31–33—female); 34–40—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. (34, 36, 39–40—lateral view; 35—dorsal view; 37—dorsolateral view; 38—face; 34–38—male; 39–40—female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772391/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 26–27, 32</figureCitation>
). Median keel usually absent; in males occasionally distinguishable only on mesonotum, in females also in middle part of face.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,908,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
Abdominal apodemes of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[497,513,1592,1606]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">nd</superScript>
tergite in male with long rounded lobes bent inwards and separated by oval notch (
<figureCitation box="[159,300,1628,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–117" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1860,1885]" captionTargetBox="[246,1350,176,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[236,1352,166,1840]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 82–117. 82–94—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori; 95–108—M. nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 109–117—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. 82–83, 95–96—male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 84–85, 97–98―the 2nd sternite; 86–87, 99–100, 110—penis, lateral view; 88–89, 101–102, 113—style; 90—pygofer processes, back view; 91–92, 103–104, 111—pygofer process, lateral view; 105, 112—pygofer process, dorsolateral view; 93, 106–107, 114–115—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 94, 108, 116–117—female 7th sternite; 109—male 2nd abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 95–96</figureCitation>
); sternal apodemes triangular, strongly converging, separated by more or less rounded notch (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 82–117" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1860,1885]" captionTargetBox="[246,1350,176,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[236,1352,166,1840]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 82–117. 82–94—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori; 95–108—M. nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 109–117—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. 82–83, 95–96—male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 84–85, 97–98―the 2nd sternite; 86–87, 99–100, 110—penis, lateral view; 88–89, 101–102, 113—style; 90—pygofer processes, back view; 91–92, 103–104, 111—pygofer process, lateral view; 105, 112—pygofer process, dorsolateral view; 93, 106–107, 114–115—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 94, 108, 116–117—female 7th sternite; 109—male 2nd abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 97–98</figureCitation>
). Penis in side view slender, evenly tapering apically (
<figureCitation box="[835,987,1665,1691]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–117" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1860,1885]" captionTargetBox="[246,1350,176,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[236,1352,166,1840]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 82–117. 82–94—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori; 95–108—M. nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 109–117—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. 82–83, 95–96—male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 84–85, 97–98―the 2nd sternite; 86–87, 99–100, 110—penis, lateral view; 88–89, 101–102, 113—style; 90—pygofer processes, back view; 91–92, 103–104, 111—pygofer process, lateral view; 105, 112—pygofer process, dorsolateral view; 93, 106–107, 114–115—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 94, 108, 116–117—female 7th sternite; 109—male 2nd abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 99–100</figureCitation>
). Style tip thin, pointed, bent inwards at almost right angle (
<figureCitation box="[367,531,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–117" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1860,1885]" captionTargetBox="[246,1350,176,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[236,1352,166,1840]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 82–117. 82–94—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori; 95–108—M. nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 109–117—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. 82–83, 95–96—male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 84–85, 97–98―the 2nd sternite; 86–87, 99–100, 110—penis, lateral view; 88–89, 101–102, 113—style; 90—pygofer processes, back view; 91–92, 103–104, 111—pygofer process, lateral view; 105, 112—pygofer process, dorsolateral view; 93, 106–107, 114–115—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 94, 108, 116–117—female 7th sternite; 109—male 2nd abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 101–102</figureCitation>
). Similarly to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[689,871,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippodameia">
<emphasis box="[689,871,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">M. hippodameia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, pygofer lobes with strongly sclerotized ribs along back margins. Pygofer process unusually short, with straight distal part (
<figureCitation box="[966,1132,1736,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–117" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1860,1885]" captionTargetBox="[246,1350,176,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[236,1352,166,1840]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 82–117. 82–94—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori; 95–108—M. nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 109–117—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. 82–83, 95–96—male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 84–85, 97–98―the 2nd sternite; 86–87, 99–100, 110—penis, lateral view; 88–89, 101–102, 113—style; 90—pygofer processes, back view; 91–92, 103–104, 111—pygofer process, lateral view; 105, 112—pygofer process, dorsolateral view; 93, 106–107, 114–115—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 94, 108, 116–117—female 7th sternite; 109—male 2nd abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 103–105</figureCitation>
). 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1166,1182,1736,1750]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor with 6–7 preapical teeth (
<figureCitation box="[434,600,1773,1800]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–117" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1860,1885]" captionTargetBox="[246,1350,176,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[236,1352,166,1840]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 82–117. 82–94—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori; 95–108—M. nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 109–117—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. 82–83, 95–96—male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 84–85, 97–98―the 2nd sternite; 86–87, 99–100, 110—penis, lateral view; 88–89, 101–102, 113—style; 90—pygofer processes, back view; 91–92, 103–104, 111—pygofer process, lateral view; 105, 112—pygofer process, dorsolateral view; 93, 106–107, 114–115—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 94, 108, 116–117—female 7th sternite; 109—male 2nd abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 106–107</figureCitation>
). Female 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[721,734,1772,1786]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">th</superScript>
sternite of usual shape, triangular, with small shallow notch on hind margin (
<figureCitation box="[302,400,1809,1835]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–117" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1860,1885]" captionTargetBox="[246,1350,176,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[236,1352,166,1840]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 82–117. 82–94—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori; 95–108—M. nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 109–117—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. 82–83, 95–96—male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 84–85, 97–98―the 2nd sternite; 86–87, 99–100, 110—penis, lateral view; 88–89, 101–102, 113—style; 90—pygofer processes, back view; 91–92, 103–104, 111—pygofer process, lateral view; 105, 112—pygofer process, dorsolateral view; 93, 106–107, 114–115—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 94, 108, 116–117—female 7th sternite; 109—male 2nd abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Fig. 108</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,908,2015]" box="[199,942,1844,1872]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
Body length (including tegmina): 
<specimenCount box="[580,603,1845,1871]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 3.1–3.5 mm; 
<specimenCount box="[765,786,1845,1871]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, 3.5–3.7 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="371" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,908,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1880,1907]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnavuori, 1978" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[476,766,1881,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhea">
<emphasis box="[476,564,1881,1907]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">M. rhea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[571,766,1881,1907]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of female 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1048,1061,1880,1894]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">th</superScript>
sternite. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnavuori, 1978" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tithonia">
<emphasis box="[1312,1436,1881,1907]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">M. tithonia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[151,347,1917,1943]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnavuori, 1978" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[403,752,1917,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerophila">
<emphasis box="[403,548,1917,1943]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">M. xerophila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[556,752,1917,1943]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of dark pattern on pro- and mesonotum. Much smaller than 
<emphasis box="[296,676,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName authorityName="China" authorityYear="1925" box="[296,479,1954,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octopunctata">M. octopunctata</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName box="[512,676,1953,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pondoensis">M. pondoensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,908,2015]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,153,395]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="371" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
Differs from all species from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[581,696,1989,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuscula">
<emphasis box="[581,696,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">minuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group for which descriptions of the genitalia are available (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="371" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 63–81</figureCitation>
) by the shape of style tip and shorter pygofer process. In addition, differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1141,1294,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bitaeniata">
<emphasis box="[1141,1294,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">M. bitaeniata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippodameia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">M. hippodameia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by smaller size. Penis is more slender than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnavuori, 1978" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[776,1131,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuscula">
<emphasis box="[776,927,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">M. minuscula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[934,1131,189,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
