<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="371" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,297,323]" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">Etymology.</emphasis>
According to ancient Greek mythology, Nikippa was one of the daughters of Hippodamia (alternative spelling of Hippodamea) and Pelops. The new species is named “nikippa” because it is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippodameia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="371">M. hippodameia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is distinctly smaller.
</paragraph>
